I"÷<p>I just wanted to document the creation process of creating this website. The goal of this site is to share what I do with you. I will be promoting my woodworking projects and everything I deem showable of the free time stuff going on here.</p>

<p>So I needed a simple vessel to present that. Here we are with the technicals:</p>

<ul>
  <li>Installing Ruby on a Mac. used chruby and ruby-install <a href="https://thoughtbot.com/blog/psa-do-not-use-system-ruby">Link</a></li>
  <li>Installing Bundler as per jeryll website procedure</li>
  <li>Installing Jekyll (text to static website) <a href="https://jekyllrb.com">link</a></li>
  <li>Jekyll theme Clean Blog</li>
  <li>Using atom as my IDE <a href="https://atom.io">link</a></li>
  <li>Integrating git as my version control for the project</li>
  <li>Using github.io to host the website with a custom domain name</li>
  <li>Modifying the cname of my domain name to point to github servers</li>
  <li>Creating this page to document the whole thing</li>
</ul>
